Yemen Protests Cost Economy About $8 Billion, Al Hayat Reports

-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 
2011-08-14T05:39:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-14/yemen-protests-cost-economy-about-8-billion-al-hayat-reports.html
Protests in Yemen have cost the
economy about $8 billion this year until the end of July, Al
Hayat newspaper reported, citing Trade Minister Hisham Sharaf.  Tourism revenue may plunge to less than $50 million in 2011
from $1.1 billion last year, the London-based newspaper quoted
the minister as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaa Shahine in Dubai at 
 asalha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  